    "body": "So the thing is that in practice, executing this code costs more gas than anyone can pay. Taking the gas costs into account makes it very hard to randomly generate code that actually runs in a meaningful way. Because of that, I would propose to keep ignoring the gas costs and instead make `mstore(0xffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffff, ...)` work and also not truncate any data.",
